[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Considering method registration**\n\nI’m pondering whether ELSupport.class.getMethod requires method registration for Object methods. Maybe the JDK metadata is accessible, which could mean no need for additional metadata. But what about if the method is private? It seems that bindMethod would map Object.toString as a function. It calls loadMethod(\"toString\") and retrieves the public Object.toString. So, I wonder if that call on ELSupport.class.getMethod(\"toString\") permits access to the inherited Object method. Is that even allowed in a native context?", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0d98600daee34c4e0169f27fcc08ac81938ec88ac2dc879a1f\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp8n_kF0Ey_Cg-NqVyq-gQRC6fVORDmsU6j1nICDDPB7tboeB5rBEQrpaJ9a416L2U2a9mmenD1uSg0pzLdChadQCGZm-B3F-URMB5CHcGutDPMZ2crlN4NW58mg44owHjGxzwfikwPmtMdmmjlLjo8Sl3CaY2qFBYnPKp29gzmp9ce-rO1eIZwzPGz2tS9-GO-bTvKXXlU5sw7ZNWHAclGceXhFs1URM_eDlI8zNV-F2wXyQHE0KVjs9P-6aTiIvoAI2-wt0IVpILGmmWf-6UfO8BjeaxXOA7B5QgM4Idv9n06kLCqL8BldCZCXFWF-ESoTB7oZVpw3yTBnTKSv6vSVmG-ZhdrSWSM74bw0RB6acQ928_YVK2MYDcCpMSqIUIc-ZYt2zYN07AkBXmR6C3VYF9RDtynYR4lIe_-CDQWDoTRlysIwKyjPJRkYsCKsPKxOheEJdZEJpHCfL0JeZco-mGbyXuxlTm1TsW3hYyEnwNUqUsQK9V3EenlrTWtBwI92OInhUCvmov_yilYAUTUldPSJIARJAzQQ0A5DdBMen5_eIWxXDzD-pI8Ks9qvxBsFD6sPbY-IeIdTvcJcalkru51CmAb_IAXiGBodAsI2LEyOynxvWPf_NxBZKBrZpWut4Lbyi8TfBIwiFgPTX4-LuTScMBuHtWCYO0AofVwRMTYT1XPyn4FtLWnlHrPoINHr5NYNXiVB6bJIAsv7VnLiAURvG3YVrxjjaH_RoIt772O6W2Gz0ylpuN0jBYYIKvDtU9ATq16Gy6Qqsb3iTgM_oZnaIZZio4RSx0WOeyPzPE8W3x8T3bGBMc5Hab4fPPyjDN0yt2ooBfk3qCulURQ-rM_hvyrTItkGoEiKDqfyTCPOpFhkGIxxBPnumDq31y4NvUXJeZgsX8aDo139Mhg-3tHrLNoPRnQiyiRHTOty54I5FUjjMnephsYFChcf-zlbQvILl6KnRJleKKeoQgDLeSZLKNrO6SxfRq8vFLCz2PEyVXyY77vde8bjN40VzYZRAbgj5NeahHnX5zaQwyogeY8jMxmKpitX0sQJN8r3bEZ5p3x5-vx0meXupKzfHzjiQ9q0a4GTDLgSCetSB7g5Bb5trA7mnU3RveFR5XJNn7o5tBOIlv7U1WLrpnO37osWE2mMH0l1Xs7CDGRDxs5kQvb1KQ-vj